The Bright Blue paint flashes like lightning and the engine roars like thunder when this Plymouth flies by.This example was born as a Belvedere II and has since gone through a complete transformation, like a butterfly getting its wings.  The original slant-six engine was removed and this fire-breathing 440 was stuffed in its place. description: For sale in out Nashville showroom is a long and lustrous 1967 Plymouth Belvedere. This 1967 Plymouth Belvedere for sale  is the best of both worlds! Your 1967 Belvedere can be rolling with the  top up and you can enjoy the pleasantries of a cruiser on a not so pleasant day or with the power automatic top down you can enjoy with other world of cars and let the wind blow in your hair. This canvas top is not to be compared to vintage, from the looks of this top It has many more years of life for the owner to enjoy. This 1967 Plymouth for sale is powered by a stout 383 CID V8 that is backed by an automatic 3 speed transmission that is ready to beat the streets or the honda in the other lane! This 1967 Plymouth has many options that are taken for granted in our new and late model cars. Lets for a second go over some things that we are so used to that we do not know that they are special, power brakes? Yes I said power brakes as when they first started rolling cars or wagons to start they featured a steel ring around the wheel and when the driver or operator wanted to stop the wagon he would push on the handle and a wooden pad would pinch this ring. WOW.  Now we have power brakes like this Plymouth features, press the pedal and this beauty stops with ease all while rolling on Mag 500's wrapped with radial tires.  The Plymouth for sale is also featuring power steering, another option taken for granted as older vehicles had oversized steering wheels to make up for non power steering. This 1967 for sale shows a beautiful exterior color of blue on the outside with a matching black interior to match the top. Features on this 1967 Plymouth Belvedere include: am/fm radio, automatic convertible top, power brakes, powers steering, seat belts, anti-theft system and radial tires. For more information call the Nashville showroom at 615-213-1800 or email us at Nashville@gatewayclassiccars.com
